Round 1:
[Patient] What foods can I eat to help my heart failure?
[Healthcare Educator] Focus on fruits, veggies, whole grains, and lean protein.

Round 2:
[Patient] Can I still have fried foods?
[Healthcare Educator] Limit fried foods, opt for baked or grilled options instead.

Round 3:
[Patient] How about salt in my diet?
[Healthcare Educator] Reduce salt intake to help manage heart failure.

Round 4:
[Patient] Are there any specific foods I should avoid?
[Healthcare Educator] Limit processed foods, sugary drinks, and high-fat dairy products.

Round 5:
[Patient] Any tips for eating out at restaurants?
[Healthcare Educator] Look for menu options with lean protein, veggies, and whole grains. Avoid fried and heavily salted dishes.